From: DICOMKit Integration <copilot@github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Int32 overflow crash in DecoderPipeline.applyDequantization

The dequantization step in DecoderPipeline crashes with:
  "Fatal error: Double value cannot be converted to Int32
   because the result would be greater than Int32.max"

when `Double(coeff) * stepSize` exceeds the Int32 range.

This occurs because `Int32(Double(...))` uses a trapping conversion.
The fix clamps the product to the Int32 range before conversion.

Reproduction:
  1. Encode a 16x16 8-bit gradient image with J2KEncoder (lossless)
  2. Decode the resulting codestream with J2KDecoder
  3. Crash at J2KDecoderPipeline.swift:847

---
 Sources/J2KCodec/J2KDecoderPipeline.swift | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Sources/J2KCodec/J2KDecoderPipeline.swift b/Sources/J2KCodec/J2KDecoderPipeline.swift
index 6097d27..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/Sources/J2KCodec/J2KDecoderPipeline.swift
+++ b/Sources/J2KCodec/J2KDecoderPipeline.swift
@@ -843,8 +843,9 @@ struct DecoderPipeline: Sendable {
             let stepSize = metadata.quantizationSteps[key] ?? 1.0
 
-            // Dequantize coefficients
+            // Dequantize coefficients (clamped to Int32 range to prevent overflow)
             let dequantized = info.coefficients.map { coeff in
-                Int32(Double(coeff) * stepSize)
+                let product = Double(coeff) * stepSize
+                let clamped = max(Double(Int32.min), min(Double(Int32.max), product))
+                return Int32(clamped)
             }
